Meanwhile, Mary wanted to know what she looked like, so she went to the town's painter, Mike, and asked him to make a portrait of her. But when Mike tried to paint her face, something strange happened. His mind suddenly went blank, and his hand holding the brush wouldn't stop shaking. It frustrated him because he was just one step away from finishing the portrait. Mary then walked up to the painting and saw the empty, faceless space. She immediately lifted Mike and set him on top of the cabinet, telling him to calm down. Mike was terrified by the move, broke into a cold sweat, realizing what she really Was and thought about escaping, but Mary was already blocking the doorway, demanding that he continue painting her portrait. Mike had no choice but to obey. Mary even warned him that if he didn't finish within five minutes, she would drain every drop of liquid from his body. With no other option, Mike blindfolded himself and tried to paint purely by feeling. When he finally opened his eyes and saw the finished portrait, he was stunned. Mary also looked at the painting and was captivated by the beautiful face. But what she didn't know was that the portrait Mike painted was not of her. It was of the human girl Anna.

voice_to_text: To save people, he lay flat on a speeding skateboard. Then his teammate released the skateboard's connector, sending it sliding rapidly beneath the passenger filled bus behind them. Because terrorists had planted multiple bombs under the bus, if the speed dropped below 50, the bombs would detonate. So the police could only use this method to send bomb disposal expert Jimmy under the bus. With the bus driver's cooperation, he successfully reached the bomb's location. Drawing on years of bomb disposal experience, Jimmy quickly found the bomb's control wire. But just as he was about to cut it, the high speed skateboard suddenly hit a piece of rubber on the road. It instantly lost control. Even the safety rope up front couldn't hold it back. In the critical moment, Jimmy grabbed onto the bus chassis in time, avoiding being crushed by the spinning wheels. But the danger wasn't over. If this continued, his strength would soon run out. Worse still, the massive pulling force had snapped the safety rope connecting the skateboard. By now, no matter how strong Jimmy's arms were, he could no longer stop the skateboard from sliding backward. Watching death draw closer and closer, Jimmy directly jammed the screwdriver into the fuel tank to use as a handhold. With his other hand, he grabbed an iron frame on the chassis. This finally freed his entire body from the skateboard. Passengers on the bus quickly opened the floor and pulled Jimmy up together, but this wasn't the time. To celebrate, yet the fuel tank had been punctured and was now leaking continuously. In less than 10 minutes, the bus would stop and everyone would be killed in the explosion. Since they couldn't defuse the bomb, the police brought in a flatbed truck to drive alongside the bus, hoping to rescue the passengers this way. Only the first passenger was lucky. When it was the second passenger's turn, the bomber suddenly triggered a bomb under the door. The step was instantly blown open with a hole and the woman fell from the bus and lost her life. Jimmy felt very guilty about this, but it also made him realize there must be a surveillance camera installed in the bus. That's how the bomber knew their every move. Sure enough, after some searching, he found a pinhole camera lens in a corner above the door. After learning this, captain quickly had the radio station intercept transmission signals in the area and replaced them with footage of the current bus, then loop it, they hoped to fool the bomber. In reality, they had already started the rescue operation. With the efforts of the police and Jimmy, all passengers were soon transferred to the bus on the other side. The bomber didn't notice anything unusual. Now only the driver and Jimmy remained on the bus. To escape alive, Jimmy used a metal rod to hold down the gas pedal, then tied one end of a rope to the steering wheel and the Other end to an iron plate. Then they lay on the iron plate and escaped from under the bus. The bus changed its direction due to the rope's pulling force, and finally crashed into an abandoned airplane and exploded.

He told the nurse to listen carefully to every word he was about to say, because only then could she clear herself of suspicion. The the old man didn't want her family to fall apart because of him. Once she was out of the surveillance zone, the old man told her to park the car on the roadside, then returned through the backyard gate because the family dog knew her and wouldn't bark. But to avoid everyone's sight, she had to climb up to the third floor using the lattice fence outside the wall, but she accidentally broke one of the bars. When she came back, the old man told her to put on his pajamas and hat. He knew his youngest son smoked at this time every night and successfully made him think it was his father. This way she had a witness, which was enough to clear her from being the prime suspect. But the girl had one fatal flaw she would throw up whenever she lied. The old man told her not to lie, then she could tell only part of the truth. Then the girl went back the same way, but as soon as she came down, she ran into the family's great grandmother. Luckily, the old woman had bad eyesight and mistook the girl for her great grandson and asked why he came back again under the cover of Darkness. The girl finally returned home, but the next day, when the butler opened the door, he saw the old man's throat was slit and a bloody knife lay on the floor. voice_to_text: My brother and I get into a car accident. My heart is ruptured. I need emergency surgery. But my mother, the hospital director, calls every available doctor to my brother's room. He only has a few scrapes, yet she orders a full body scan for him while I lie there bleeding out. I beg her to help me, but she snaps, visibly annoyed. Can't you stop fighting for attention for once? You're brother almost injured a bone. In the end, I die on the operating table. But after the news of my death breaks, my mother, who has always hated me, completely, loses her mind. In the final three minutes of my life, my soul drifted to my mother's side. She was sitting beside my younger brother Felix Goodman's hospital bed, her face filled with worry as she prayed. Felix, please don't scare me like this. Wake up, okay? My father stood nearby, his face twisted in fury. If Sean had done his job and protected him, Felix wouldn't be in this state. Just wait. I'm going to beat him to death. I stood and watched at the side, bitterness rising in my chest. Dad, there's no need for that. I'm almost dead. Not that you guys would care. At that moment, the doctors were gathered around Felix's bed in a circle. After confirming that his injuries were only scrapes and nothing major, one of the older doctors finally dared to bring me up. He asked cautiously, Miss Blanchard, are You sure we shouldn't check on Sean? His injuries from the car crash seem very serious. Mom's gentle expression instantly turned into one of disgust as she roared, what's he trying to pull now? Playing dead? Doesn't he realize what he's done to his brother? I stared at her, stunned. Though my heart had already stopped, it's still somehow throbbed with pain. I was their son, too. Did they really not care about me at all? Suddenly mom picked up her phone and dialed my number. A nurse brought the phone to my ear, and instead of hearing the concern I had hoped for, all I heard was contempt on Goodman. When are you going to crawl out of bed and apologize to your brother? My heart instantly turned cold as whatever hope I had left withered away. Of course, she never cared about me. Come to think of it, when I was first brought into the hospital, I had begged mom to save me. But all she said was, do you have to fight for attention, even at a time like this? Don't you realize that your brother nearly broke a bone? Then she turned and walked away without a second glance, taking the entire medical team with her to tend to Felix. Could she have the capacity to love me? The nurse, unable to bear it any longer, took the phone and said, Miss Blanchard, Sean can't hang on much longer. But mom, still convinced that I was Faking it, let out a mocking laugh. How much did that brat pay you to act along with him? I can't believe he's capable of something like this. Just as she finished speaking, Felix, who had been acting unconscious the whole time, finally woke up. He faked a weak voice and asked, Mom, Dad, how's Sean? As mom looked at the obedient, considerate Felix lying on the bed, her expression twisted into even deeper contempt. Sean, why can't you be more like your brother? He's hurt because of you, and yet he's still worried about you. If you don't get here in the next three minutes to apologize, don't bother ever showing your face to me again. She then hung up, her chest heaving with anger. Dad, standing beside her, looked clearly displeased. Why bother calling him? Isn't it enough that he nearly got Felix killed? Felix lowered his head, trying to hide the smug look in his eyes. He put on a guilty expression before looking up at them. Mom, dad, don't be mad at him. Sean has just never forgiven me for getting the overseas scholarship instead of him. I understand why he hates me. I couldn't help but laugh. Even in my death, Felix was still trying to sow discord between me and my parents. However, my parents would never see through him. In their eyes, he would always be the better son, and they would never think about the true reason to the car accident. Just As expected, Mom's face immediately turned cold. What's the point of sending someone that selfish to study abroad? Who knows how twisted he'd become after being abroad? Felix gently said. Mom, don't be angry. I'm sure Sean has his reasons. Mom's expression immediately softened. Felix, you're too kind. That's why Sean keeps taking advantage of you. That was always Felix's strength, knowing exactly what to say to win our parents hearts. I knew that even if I stood right in front of them and told them all of Felix's cruel behavior over the years, only slap me across the face and accuse me of making things up, saying that I was just jealous of him. After all these years, I had gotten used to it. In the middle of their conversation, my older sister, Ashley Goodman, burst into the room. Her footsteps were hurried as she anxiously rushed to check on Felix. The moment she heard about the accident, she immediately flew in from another state without a second thought. And just like my parents, she only cared about Felix once she confirmed he was okay. Ashley let out a sigh of relief before fuming. I've always said that Sean is a curse to our family. Ever since Felix was born, he's been hurting him again and again. Felix took the opportunity to act pitiful. Don't be angry, ash. I'm sure Sean didn't mean to hurt me. The whole family burst into an uproar upon hearing this. Dad slammed the Table. What? He actually caused the car accident to hurt you? Mom clenched her teeth. That bastard! I'll make him pay! The look in Ashley's eyes was venomous as she wished she could rip me into pieces. Felix flinched as though he realized things had gone too far and they might start questioning the story. He hurriedly said to them, please don't be mad at Sean, okay? Maybe I remembered it wrong. No matter what, he's still my brother. He wouldn't do something like that. Ashley gently tapped his forehead. You're just too naive. You have no idea how evil some people can be. At this point, mom chimed in, it's truly a blessing to have a son like you. Alright, I'll listen to you. Let's forget about that ungrateful brat and focus on getting you well again. The warm, golden light of the setting sun spilled across Felix's hospital bed. Watching the four of them together, a happy, United family, I felt an indescribable ache in my chest. In that moment, I realized how out of place my soul truly was. It was as if I wasn't one of them at all. Like I was just a stray dog that wandered into their home. I wanted to leave, but my spirit was bound tightly to Mom's side. I couldn't speak. I could only watch and endure their contempt in silence. Few days later, under the family's meticulous care, Felix was discharged from the hospital. Mom was busy packing his Things. While dad had already parked the car right outside the hospital door, afraid Felix might have to walk even a single extra step. And Ashley wouldn't even let him put on his shoes by himself on the way home, mom muttered irritably, Sean is really something else. He didn't even visit his brother at the hospital even once, let alone apologize. I'm going to teach him a lesson once we get home. Dad glanced at mom and said coldly, I told you keeping him at home was asking for trouble. Sooner or later, something bad was bound to happen. Hearing the words teach him a lesson left me feeling a complicated mix of emotions. Long buried memories came flooding back into my mind. Since I was young, mom had always favored Felix. I was expected to always give into him. It was all because on the day Felix was born, I had accidentally spilled water, causing mom to slip and go into premature labor. The sight of him lying in the incubator broke my entire family's hearts. Dad had smacked me so hard that my eardrum burst. You're a jinx! You're. Her brother nearly died on the day he was born because of you! Lying weakly in the hospital bed, mom had looked at me with eyes full of disappointment. Then, in elementary school, dad had beaten me so badly that I couldn't get out of bed for three days. Just because I fought with Felix over a toy. Car! It was my favorite toy. Even though what had come as a freebie along with the gift dad bought for Felix during a business trip, it had become my most cherished possession. But Felix, who already had boxes full of toy cars, insisted on fighting me for that one. In the tug of war, he suddenly screamed and burst into tears. Mom rushed over distressed and hugged him while crying and yelling at me. Sean Goodman, your brother has already suffered so much because of you. What more do you want from him? It wasn't me! Before I could even explain, Felix squeezed out a few tears and said, mom, don't be angry. It was my fault. I shouldn't have made trouble by fighting with Sean over a toy. When dad got home and saw that scene, he immediately pulled me aside and started beating me. A cold hearted kid like you doesn't deserve to stay in this house. Keep you here is just waiting for a disaster to happen. I cried and begged him to stop, but the more I cried, the more convinced dad was that I was faking it and the harder he hit. Mom and Ashley just stood at a distance, watching coldly. It was as if I was their enemy and they wouldn't be satisfied until dad beat me to death. From that day on, whenever I made Felix cry, it would mean receiving scoldings or beatings from my parents. Eventually, I stopped fighting Felix, for their love, stopped trying to explain and stop trying to get close. And now they left me cold and lifeless on the operating table. As soon as they got home, Felix sloped onto the couch. The moment he said he was hungry, Ashley eagerly went into the kitchen, excited to show off her new found cooking skills. Normally too delicate to cook, she was now scrolling through her phone for nutritious meal plans. Afraid of causing Felix to have an upset stomach, dad presented him with the latest luxury gaming console, saying it was a welcome home gift to celebrate his cheating death. Mom had already cleaned Felix's room thoroughly and filled it with air purifying plants, saying that fresh air was good for his recovery. Felix simply lounged on the couch and played games. Yet that was enough to tug at the heartstrings of the entire family. Meanwhile, my soul was trailing quietly behind them. This house, once so familiar, now felt ice cold. Suddenly, the door bell rang. Standing at the door with someone I knew all too well, my girlfriend, Caitlin Winter. She stepped inside and immediately fussed over Felix's condition. Mr. And Mrs. Goodman, I heard Felix was discharged today. I brought some supplements for him. Felix instantly dropped the game controller, putting on a shy smile. Caitlin, you didn't have to. I'm already feeling much better. Caitlin flashed him a sweet smile. Usually cold and aloof with me, she was now gentle and Caring with Felix, I watched her, an unfamiliar feeling rising in my chest. Suddenly she asked, where's Sean? If she hadn't brought me up, I doubt anyone would have even remembered I existed. When my name was mentioned, Mom's face darkened. Why are you bringing up that ungrateful brat? After I scolded him the other day, he didn't even bother coming home. It's just as well. Since he likes staying out so much, he can stay away forever. The house feels peaceful without him causing trouble every day. Caitlin quickly nodded. It's better if he doesn't come back. Don't want him disturbing Felix's rest. Ashley walked out, holding some supplements and said playfully, so, have you decided when to break up with Sean? If you don't move fast, someone else might snatch Felix away. Caitlin lowered her head shyly. I was actually planning to talk to Felix about it today. A stinging sensation welled up in my throat. I let out a self mocking laugh and turned away, not wanting to watch any longer. I had long grown used to the feeling of being unloved anyway. After dinner, mom grew irritable for some reason. She returned to her room alone and began searching through her phone. I walked over to look. She was looking for my number, calling it again and again, but of course there was no answer. Eventually she slammed her phone down in frustration. You won't even answer my calls now? Do you think anyone actually cares? About you. I wanted to tell her I'm dead. There's no way for me to answer your call. But then she called the nurse from the hospital. Did Sean tell you what kind of stunt he's trying to pull? Tell him to stop being so shameless and come back to apologize to his brother. Then maybe I'll consider letting him come home. There was a brief silence on the other end before the reply came. Miss Blanchard, Sean passed away a week ago. His heart was ruptured in the car accident. But you had called all the doctors to Felix's room, so there was no one left to operate on him.

voice_to_text: Jackie Chan happened to pass by and effortlessly pulled a stranger out of danger. The woman turned out to be a reporter pursuing evidence against a criminal syndicate. The gang scattered, hunting for both her and the incriminating footage she had captured. Using a delivery truck as temporary cover, Jackie seized the brief opening to slip away unseen. The thugs crawled across the ground, searching, yet still failed to track them down. Just as the pursuers were about to give up and sweep another area, Jackie caught the gaze of one of them through the rearview mirror. Reacting instantly, he yanked open the canvas hood, slamming the thug against the side of the truck. They turned and tried to escape quietly, only to run straight into another enemy lurking around the corner. Jackie handed over his pistol to divert the attacker's attention, though the weapon was completely empty. More reinforcements arrived, forcing them to flee again until they hit a dead end. He lifted the reporter onto the top of an iron gate, then squeezed himself through the bars at the very last moment, finally shaking the mob, at least for now. After rescuing this complete stranger, he simply nodded goodbye and the two parted ways. But the thugs climbed over the gate, still determined to hunt Jackie down. I don't even know her, he muttered. Meanwhile, they assumed the boy nearby was absorbed in his video game.

voice_to_text: His name is Jackie Chan, a top level specialist known for tracking the most dangerous criminals. This time he is hunting a killer, the man people call the Wolf King. The Wolf King once raised a group of children and trained them in every skill he mastered. Ten years later, those children have become highly capable operatives. Each one developed a unique specialty. Some became masters of disguise, others experts in altering their appearance and some could even switch genders flawlessly. Behind them stands a formidable tech support team with the Wolf King pulling the strings from the shadows, making their entire operation almost unstoppable. Ordinary officers don't stand a chance against them. But this time they ran into him. After picking up the Wolf King's trail, he assigned a female officer to tail the target. Her cover looked natural enough at first. At the moment they crossed paths, she had already been exposed. Fortunately, he noticed everything in time. voice_to_text: This one has a lot of people up in arms. Two girls were trying to board a United flight in Denver when the gate agent stopped them, deeming their spandex leggings were inappropriate. The outrage began at Denver airport Sunday when two girls were denied entry onto a United flight by the gate agent. The reason, they were wearing spandex leggings. Passenger Shannon Watts tweeting, she's forcing them to change or put dresses on over leggings or they can't board. Since when does United Police women's clothing? United immediately responded, we do have the right to refuse transport for passengers who are barefoot or not properly clothed. The reaction on social media, fast and furious. Since when are leggings inappropriate? Is United Airlines fashion police or misogynist? United later clarified the girls were traveling on the airline's pass program which provides free flights for relatives and friends of United employees. The airline told us it has stricter dress code requirements for these non revenue passengers. United's policy does seem a bit more sexist than other airlines.

voice_to_text: Help! Help! Help! Oh, my god! Oh, my god! This man might have to pay $300,000 for saving a baby's life after he accidentally fractured the baby's arm during the rescue. The baby's mother sued him for that amount to cover medical expenses. In Orlando, Florida, David Walker was walking down the street when he heard a scream coming from a building. Looking up, he saw a baby falling from a fourth floor balcony. Without thinking, he stretched out his arms and managed to catch the baby just before it hit the ground. He then handed the baby to its mother, who ran over to receive it, thanking David for his bravery. However, three days later, David received a legal notice. The mother accused him of breaking the baby's arm and demanded $300,000 in compensation. In court, David, in tears, explained that he only wanted to save the child and never intended to harm him. His lawyer argued that under Florida law, he should be considered a savior and not an aggressor, as his actions were not guilty. But the judge and jury decided that even though David was covered by the good Samaritan law, the consequences of his actions were severe, so they sentenced him to pay $100,000 in compensation. David, disappointed with the ruling, said he would never again intervene in other people's problems. Do you think this trial was fair? Let us know your opinion in the comments.

voice_to_text: What happened when I realized I was everyone's backup friend at my own wedding? On my wedding day, I'm standing at the altar thinking, this is actually perfect. Thirty people I love most in the world are here after years of planning, and I'm marrying my best friend. Then I noticed my maid of honor keeps looking at her phone. She's holding her bouquet with one hand and her phone is in the other. I keep trying to make eye contact with her to put it away, but she's still scrolling, eyes glued to the screen. My husband squeezes my hand, and I try to focus on this moment. But I can see the blue light in the corner of my eye and hear her nails against the screen. The ceremony ends and the bridal group is walking back down the aisle. I'm greeting people when I see all of my bridesmaids clustered near the exit of a venue. I drift toward their direction and hear one of them say, we can make the rest of this wedding quick, right? The ceremony is done, so dinner next? Another bridesmaid nods. Yeah, we should be out by six, easy. My stomach groans. I stop walking so suddenly my husband almost trips over my dress. You okay? He asks. I nod, but I'm not. We planned this reception to go until nine. Once we're outside, my maid of honor appears next to me, already changed into jeans. Hey, babe. Amazing ceremony. Listen, I might have to leave early tonight. I just stare at her. Leave early? You're my maid of honor. This is my wedding. We sent save the dates 14 months ago. What could possibly. I can't even finish the sentence as my brain won't let me complete that thought. She does this little laugh. I know. I'm so sorry. Something came up. But I'm here now, right? She's here now at my wedding reception that we're 10 minutes into. My husband pulls me aside. What's going on? I pull out my phone because I can't shake this feeling that someone is plotting against us. I open Instagram and see a post from my college friend. A few days ago she posted, sorry I can't attend a loved one's wedding. Work sucks. One hour ago, she posted a boomerang of her blowing up balloons. Birthday bash tonight! Can't wait to see everyone at 7! I scroll down the comment section. 50 comments, all from people I know. I see my bridesmaids in the comments. All four of them. One person says, wrong account, girl. I didn't know my college friend had a second account. I keep scrolling through mutual followers until I find it on the second account. Two months ago, she posted save the date for my birthday party. And the date was for my wedding today. My invitations went out 16 months ago. I scan the room and spot my cousin who is known for having all the tea I asked her outright if someone is trying to upstage my wedding. My cousin debates on answering before handing me her phone. I'm sorry. The party just sounded so epic and I didn't want to hurt you. Her phone was open to a group chat called The Birthday Party. It has 100 people in it. All my bridesmaids are there. Over half my guests are included in the chat. My maid of honor left a message five days ago saying we'll just stay for the wedding ceremony and dinner, then head out. Should make the party by 7. Someone responds, she won't mind us leaving her wedding early, right? She's always so understanding. Then my maid of honor says, should we tell her we're leaving early? Only for my college friend throwing the party to say now? Why make it awkward? Just tell her you have to go in the moment. She won't have time to process all of you leaving. I screenshot everything and text it to myself. I walk over to where my maid of honor is standing with the other bridesmaids. I'm honestly surprised she's still here. They're all huddled together, looking at someone's phone. My heart is pounding. What time are you leaving? I asked them. They look up, startled. One bridesmaid says, what? I'm not leaving. I smile and say, for the birthday party, what time are you all leaving my wedding to go? You could hear a bouquet drop. My maid of honor looks At the others for help, but they're staring at the floor. I hold up my phone, showing the screenshots of their group chat. She announced her party eight months after I sent wedding invites. You all are a C P D S to both and didn't tell me? My maid of honor stammers. We just wanted to stop by afterward, but we're here for you. One of the other bridesmaids jumps in. You're being unreasonable. We can support both of you if we feel like it. I feel like I'm watching myself from outside my body. You plan to leave my reception early without telling me? That's not being my friend. That's treating me like your backup plan. My maid of honor's eyes narrow. That's not fair. We showed up, didn't we? I and to face the whole reception. Is anyone else leaving early for the birthday party? Please go now so I know who I'm actually celebrating my special day with. The silence is horrible. Then my cousin stands up. Then my coworker. My maid of honor storms out. The other bridesmaids follow her, and I'm standing there, watching half my guests walk out the door. My husband wraps his arm around my shoulders. Well, now we know who actually cares.

El coche aceleró de repente como un automático 3 velocidades y el caos se apoderó de la escena. De pronto, chocó contra el tráfico que tenía adelante y despegó con una arrancada fulgurante. voice_to_text: Turns out that becoming invisible isn't some thrilling superpower. It's a deeply unsettling experience. The researchers poured a thick adhesive beside the man, spread it across his face, and used a fan to dry it in seconds. Once the coating hardened, they sliced a small opening and placed a custom pair of glasses on him. They assumed John would last only a few days, but no one expected him to remain trapped in the lab for so long. As the days dragged on, his his frustration grew, until he finally broke out. When he returned home, he caught a glimpse of his neighbor changing clothes, but at the last moment, she pulled the curtains shut. Staring at his own reflection, John suddenly understood. He had gained the power to disappear. And with that power, he could do almost anything he wanted. Not long after the woman finished her shower, a knock echoed through her front door. She checked outside and saw nothing, thinking it was just her imagination, until the doorbell chimed again. Confused, she opened the door only to find the hallway completely empty. But in that very moment, the unseen John had already slipped silently into her home.

voice_to_text: A little boy slipped accidentally and tumbled into a river. Thirty five years later, he awoke in the middle of a rice field in a remote village somewhere in rural China. Strangers surrounded him and the language they spoke was completely unfamiliar. The boy, terrified, fainted on the spot. The villagers quickly contacted the US Embassy. When the staff checked his clothes, they discovered a tag with a handwritten name, Jacob. Astonishingly, the boy could recall his entire family address from memory. Soon after, he was sent back to the United States, delivered to the house he had written down. Detective Malik assigned to follow the case. Unable to believe the address actually existed, he knocked and a man in his 70s opened the door. Malik asked if the man had ever lost a son. The elder informed him that his child had died 35 years ago. But when he saw the boy, he froze. Jacob suddenly blurted out a nonsensical phrase rushed out at the speed of lightning like millions of miles per hour, like frogs spinning in a blender. The old man responded instinctively to the riddle. Seconds later, he realized that only he and his son had ever known this puzzle. Yet 35 years ago, he had buried his son with his own hands. The old man stood frozen, staring in disbelief.

voice_to_text: That day, I was washing my hair by the river. I didn't expect the shampoo I used to poison the fish in the water. So I tried to make a fire by rubbing two sticks together. But after an hour of trying, I still failed. Then I lit a cigarette and fell asleep on the ground. By nightfall, I finally ate some grilled fish. I had been trapped here for three days. It was the first thing I'd eaten in all that time. At night, a few pigeons ate the leftover fish, and they were poisoned, too. So that's how I got more food to eat. One day, while squatting on the ground in a daze, I accidentally found a pack of instant noodles. Inside there was still a small packet of seasoning. The picture of noodles on the package made me crave them even more. So I really wanted to eat noodles like that. First, I dug a hole in the ground. Then I searched for undigested seeds and bird droppings. After finding some, I started farming the land. I mixed the seeds with the droppings and planted them every day. I worked hard, and after six months, my crops finally grew corn. When the corn ripened, I began making noodles. I ground the corn into flour, then add water to knead the dough. After a long and complicated process, I finally made a bowl of handmade noodles. When the noodles were ready, I took out that precious packet. Of seasoning. After waiting nearly 200 days, I finally tasted those delicious noodles. At that moment, tears of joy rolled down my face. But that night, heavy rain fell. All my crops were destroyed. Even my makeshift shelter was washed away by the flood. The next morning, I stared hopelessly at the devastation. Just then, two sanitation workers appeared behind me. They came to take me off the island. I looked at them in despair, unable to say a single word.

voice_to_text: La femme qui nettoyait le miroir remarquait quelque chose d'étrange. La personne dans le vieux tableau derrière elle semblait avoir bougé. Elle se retourne à confuse, se rappelant que le visage de la femme était tourné vers la droite, mais maintenant, il était tourné vers la gauche. En y réfléchissant, elle pensa qu'il était peu probable que le tableau ait pu bouger tout seul, mais que cela devait être une illusion. Cependant, ce qui se passait ensuite fut encore plus bizarre. Dans la chambre de cathy se trouvait également un tableau ancien similaire d'une personne tenant une paire de ciseaux et un peigne. Le tableau était un peu une horreur, mais cathy essaya de l'enlever, sans succès, comme s'il ne s'agissait pas d'un tableau, mais d'une personne. La nuit, quand cathy s'endormit, le bruit de ciseaux se fit soudain entendre à côté d'elle, et, dans un clique-tige, les cheveux de cathy furent inexplicablement coupés. Le lendemain, cathy se réveilla et constata que la moitié de ses cheveux manquaient. Ses beaux cheveux longs avaient été coupés et abîmés. Cathy pensa que c'était sa sœur espiègle qui lui avait fait une farce. elle la tira du lit et était sur le point de la frapper, mais annie arriva juste à temps pour les arrêter. Cathy se plaignait à annie que sa sœur lui avait coupé les cheveux la nuit dernière, pendant son sommeil. Mais elle avait l'air innocente, car elle n'avait rien fait la nuit dernière. Annie savait comment était sa Fille cadette, mais peu importe combien elle essayait d'expliquer, annie ne l'a cru pas et exigea qu'elle s'excuse auprès de cathy, sans se rendre compte qu'elles avaient toutes les deux eu tort. La nuit suivante, cathy s'apprêtait à se brosser les cheveux et à se coucher, quand elle entendit soudain ce qui ressemblait à des ciseaux. Parce que ses cheveux avaient été coupés sans raison apparente et qu'elle était très sensible au bruit des ciseaux. Quand elle tourna la tête pour regarder derrière elle, elle vit le tableau des ciseaux et du peigne sur la table de chevet. Et maintenant, ce tableau la mettait très mal à l'aise. Alors, elle trouva un morceau de tissu blanc pour cacher le tableau. Au moment où elle s'endormait, le bruit de ciseaux qui clique se fit à nouveau entendre à côté de cathy, et une main s'étira de derrière le tissu blanc, coupant lentement les cheveux de cathy. Quand cathy se réveilla, la main retourna dans le tissu blanc et disparu. Quand cathy se réveilla, elle toucha ses cheveux coupés et pensa instantanément à sa sœur espièque. Cependant, au moment où elle allait sortir pour donner une leçon à sa sœur, elle trouva que c'était un peu déraisonnable que sa sœur n'aurait pas pu venir dans sa chambre la nuit, quand il faisait si sombre dehors. Où y avait-il quelqu'un d'autre ? dans sa chambre ? alors qu'elle se posait la question, le tissu blanc qu'elle avait utilisé pour cacher le tableau changea soudainement et On aurait dit que quelqu'un en sortait. En entendant les cris. Sa famille entra dans la chambre, et cathy s'écria et pointa du doigt le tableau au-dessus de son lit, désignant la personne dont elle parlait, qui était juste derrière elle. Comment la famille pouvait-elle croire ça ? ils pensèrent tous que cathy faisait un cauchemar. Cependant, cathy était tellement sûr d'avoir raison qu'elle montra à tout le monde que ses cheveux avaient été coupés beaucoup plus courts. En voyant cela, la famille, un peu sceptique, devient sérieuse aussi, afin que cathy n'ait plus peur. Adam voulu t'enlever le tableau, mais peu importe combien. Il essaya, le tableau ne bougea pas, comme s'il avait poussé sur le mur. Finalement, il fallut toute la force des deux hommes, adam et nick, pour retirer le tableau du mur. Il pensait que ce serait la fin de l'histoire, mais alors des choses encore plus étranges se produisirent anne dormait la nuit quand elle entendit quelqu'un courir dans la maison. elle pensa que c'était sa fille cadette qui ne dormait pas, mais quand elle sortit de sa chambre pour vérifier, elle vit un enfant sauté dans le tableau, et ce n'était pas sa fille, lucie, mais la personne du tableau originale ff.

voice_to_text: Antes de salir de la cabina, el capitán ajustó discretamente el rumbo en tres grados, esto porque el avión estaba siendo secuestrado por terroristas. No fue hasta que el control terrestre notó que la aeronave se había desviado de su ruta. Se dieron cuenta de que algo no estaba bien a bordo. Sin embargo, un veterano entre los pasajeros descubrió accidentalmente que las armas de los secuestradores estaban cargadas con balas de fogueo. Esto porque cuando los pasajeros luchaban con los secuestradores antes, un disparo se disparó por accidente, pero ninguno de los pasajeros resultó herido. Ni siquiera quedaron agujeros de bala, y la presión de la cabina tampoco había cambiado. Esto sugería que las armas probablemente estaban cargadas con balas de fogueo que solo hacen ruido pero no causan daño real. Lograban unir a todos para resistir. Podían usar su ventaja numérica para dominar a los 5 secuestradores, pero esta teoría fue rechazada por Sam. Para estar seguro, sugirió que la gente en la cabina buscara la bala que había sido disparada. Los pasajeros en esa área no la encontraban solo, entonces podrían estar seguros de que eran balas de fogueo. Con eso, el hombre gordo presionó el botón para llamar a un secuestrador. Llamó a la secuestradora, fingiendo estar mareado y queriendo ir al baño para vomitar, pero la secuestradora fue extremadamente cautelosa. No le permitieron tirar de la cadena y tuvo que dejarle ver el vómito en el inodoro. Después de entrar al baño, él inmediatamente escribió, Un mensaje en papel con un bolígrafo. Cuando la secuestradora no lo estaba mirando. Luego arrojó el papel enrollado hacia la cabina es esperando que los pasajeros en clase económica ayudaran a buscar la bala. Una mujer curiosa abrió el papel y al leer el mensaje se agachó al suelo y comenzó a buscar. Justo cuando revisaba la última fila, fue de repente vista por un secuestrador. La mujer estaba muy nerviosa y mintió diciendo que estaba buscando sus gafas. El secuestrador encontró las gafas en el suelo y se las devolvió después de regresar a su asiento. Inmediatamente encendió la luz de lectura sobre su cabeza, señalando al hombre. Esto llenó al hombre de confianza sobre cómo terminar con este desastre, pero Sam le dijo que tal vez no se había encontrado la bala y que sin pruebas suficientes, actuar apresuradamente podría hacer que los pasajeros inocentes murieran. En ese momento, una azafata escuchó su conversación y secretamente se acercó a Sam diciéndole que no hace mucho una niña había encontrado una bala en el baño. Podían averiguar cómo era la bala que la niña vio. Podrían determinar si las armas de los secuestradores tenían balas de fogueo, así que el veterano dibujó dos balas en papel. Viendo darle la nota a la niña para que las identificara y confirmara, pero había secuestradores patrullando por todas partes. No permitían que los pasajeros se movieran o hablasen. La azafata de repente pensó en una forma. Pidió a los secuestradores que Sirvieran comida a los pasajeros y explicó que en esas circunstancias, si los pasajeros se quedaban hambrientos durante mucho tiempo podría estallar un motín. Finalmente, los secuestradores aceptaron darles a todos una botella de agua y durante la distribución del agua, los dibujos de las dos balas fueron entregados con éxito a la niña. La niña abrió los dibujos y pensó por un momento, finalmente confirmando que las armas de los secuestradores efectivamente estaban cargadas con balas de fogueo. Justo cuando se preparaban para actuar. El primer objetivo era uno de los secuestradores más viejos. De repente, un pasajero expresó su descontento con los secuestradores por no ofrecer comida y de hecho comenzó a pelear físicamente con uno de ellos. Dado que los secuestradores tenían armas, nadie se atrevió a ayudar solo. Sam pensó que esta era la oportunidad perfecta, pero el hombre ahora estaba demasiado asustado para moverse, así que ahora Sam era el único que podía ser el héroe. Sam ya se había colado en la clase económica. Se deslizó entre las dos personas que peleaban y llegó a la posición más vulnerable, enfocándose en otro secuestrador más viejo. Sam aprovechó la oportunidad para emboscarlo, pero fue derribado al suelo por el hombre mayor, quien reaccionó rápidamente. Afortunadamente, con la ayuda de un pasajero lograron derribarlo. El hombre mayor recogió el arma del suelo. El pasajero estaba demasiado asustado y rápidamente corrió, pero Sam estaba muy confiado. Declaró directamente que las armas de los secuestradores tenían balas de Fogueo, el hombre mayor, se mostró muy confundido por lo que dijo. Sin embargo, lo que Sam no esperaba era que el secuestrador líder ya había sacado balas reales. Las cargó todas en el cargador y se dirigía directamente a la sección económica donde estaba el motín. De repente, un disparo resonó en la cabina. Una mujer fue alcanzada y cayó al suelo. La cabina quedó instantáneamente en silencio. Finalmente, Sam se dio cuenta de que había apostado mal

Los 2 hombres solo sacaron un par de fotos de la chica, pero al pasar junto a john cruzaron miradas. Su mirada intensa irradiaba la presencia intimidante. Un soldado de élite sintiendo la presión. Los hombres aceleraron la moto y se marcharon. Al principio john no le dio importancia, pero más tarde, mientras hacía compras con kelly, volvió a ver la misma motocicleta. Su instinto se activó de inmediato. Algo no iba bien. John pisó el acelerador y fue tras ellos sin pensarlo. Gracias a sus habilidades al volante consiguió perderlos en un semáforo en rojo. Ya de vuelta en la casa, john enfrentó a kel exigiendo explicaciones. Ella finalmente confesó la verdad. Su padre intentaba obligarla a casarse con un empresario violento para cerrar un trato. Su madre la había ayudado a escapar para evitarle ese destino. Mientras hablaban, un grupo de hombres armados entró en la propiedad. John le dijo a kelly que se escondiera y se preparó para enfrentarlo solo se acercó sigilosamente a uno de ellos y lo eliminó sin hacer ruido. Al bajar las escaleras murió que los otros guardias ya habían sido asesinados. Estos tipos venían preparados. John corrió de nuevo hacia la habitación de kelly, pero ella ya no estaba La buscó desesperado hasta que escuchó sus gritos pidiendo ayuda. Se movió rápido, sorprendió al secuestrador y lo neutralizó de inmediato. Luego tomó a kelly y a su madre y huyeron en coche. Los hombres lo siguieron sin dudar, pero en un cruce, john apareció de la nada y embistió su vehículo de costado. Aunque lograron escapar por un tiempo, john no bajó la guardia. Gracias a su entrenamiento, tiró todos los teléfonos, abandonó el coche en la carretera y subió a un autobús público con 2h mujeres. Por fin parecía que los habían perdido, pero poco después john vio algo en las noticias que heló la sangre. Lo estaban señalando como el asesino de los guardias de la finca. Buscando respuestas, contactó a su amigo kevin y juntos regresaron a la casa. Extrañamente, el lugar que antes estaba cubierto de sangre ahora estaba impecable. Revisaron las grabaciones de seguridad y lo que john vio lo dejó sin habla. El video mostraba que era él quien mataba a los guardias. Por primera vez, john empezó a dudar de sí mismo. Podía haberlo hecho de verdad porque no recordaba nada. Justo cuando la desesperación lo dominaba, kevin notó que algo en toda aquella escena no cuadraba

voice_to_text: El cabello de esta chica es una auténtica mina de oro. Cada vez que su novio toca su cabeza, rosas frescas brotan de su melena. Esa fragancia mágica enamora a quien la huele. Pero en los ojos de su novio no hay amor, solo oportunidades de negocio. De inmediato, comienza a arrancar las rosas de su cabeza y las vende a la floristería local a cambio de montones de billetes. La convierte en un campo de flores viviente, cosechando sin parar de su cabeza, ignorando por completo el sufrimiento que ella soporta. Para él no es más que un árbol de dinero que sostiene su vida de lujos. La chica, al límite de su paciencia, hierve de rabia y despierta su poder. Su cabello ya no produce rosas, sino cactus afilados y punzantes. El novio codicioso se llena de terror. Su árbol de dinero se fuma en un instante. Mientras retrocede. Presa del pánico, recibe su merecido. Cae de espaldas en un enorme matorral de cactus. En ese momento, otra mujer entra por la puerta, cargando a su novio holgazán e inútil, llevándolo como si fuera un saco de patatas. El cabello de la chica rubia se ha transformado en radiantes girasoles, símbolo de su poder recuperado. La recién llegada huele los girasoles y de pronto siente brotar su conciencia de independencia. Tira al niñato al suelo y se marcha sin mirar atrás. Inspirada por esto, la chica original finalmente comprende que tampoco necesita a ese novio codicioso. Da media Vuelta y se va, dejándolo solo en pleno colapso. Desesperado por volver a hacerse rico, el hombre intenta replicar la magia y se echa agua en su calva cabeza. Sorprendentemente funciona, un poco de yerba y una pequeña flor brotan de su cuero cabelludo, pero antes de poder impresionar a alguna nueva ricachona, entra una cebra de golpe y se come directamente todo lo que le acaba de crecer, dejándolo sin absolutamente nada.

Él es delgado, tiene una boca grande, usa calcetines raros y tiene párpados monolíneos, completamente lo opuesto a su tipo de chico. El chico la saluda de manera amigable y de repente su corazón da un vuelco para confesarle sus sentimientos. La chica decide perder peso, se envuelve las piernas en plástico y controla estrictamente su dieta. Su peso baja ciento cincuenta y dos libras a ciento treinta y tres libras, pero rápidamente lo recupera todo. La chica se niega a rendirse y sigue con su dieta extrema. Como resultado, gana veintiséis libras adicionales en lugar de perder peso. La chica queda completamente devastada. Incluso después de comenzar a trabajar, aún no tiene el valor para confesarle y siguen siendo solo amigos. Un día, la hermana menor de la chica también se enamora de este chico. La hermana le pregunta si ella y él son pareja. La chica le dice que no es su novio. Ella supone que su hermana, por estar pasada de peso, no será capaz de conquistarlo. En una parrillada, la chica ve a su hermana charlando felizmente con él. Al ver la confianza de su hermana, la chica se da cuenta de que le falta autoestima, de un amor secreto. Pasa a enamorarse en secreto del novio de su hermana. After all these years, that strange voice in his mind was so clear, was sure it wasn't a hallucination. Shut up. When they both calmed down, they realized they shared the vision. The strangest part was that even though they were 1,000 miles apart and in different time zones, they could hear each other and share each other's vision. Thus, two people with no connection became linked. To avoid disrupting their work, they agreed to talk at night. As a child, Marco had good grades, but as an adult, he took the blame for a friend and spent five years in prison. Now he lived in misery in an abandoned shack, surviving on government subsidies. The police often visited him, warning him. That if he committed another crime, he would lose his humble job washing cars. Kelly's life, on the other hand, was the complete opposite. After graduation, she quickly married a rich man to escape her parents control. She lived a luxurious life, but had to accompany her husband to events and endure luxurious stairs that her husband ignored, using Kelly's beauty for business. Her seemingly happy marriage was full of interests. That night, Marco and Kelly connected again. Years of doubt finally had an answer. A few days earlier at a party, Kelly felt a sharp pain in her shoulder for no reason. In reality, Marco at a bar had been hit by a crazy man with a stick. The sudden connection caused that the incident was similar to 20 years ago. The piercing pain, Marco still hadn't forgotten it. Kelly remembered her skiing accident. Though their lives were difficult with this ability, they became close friends. At 15, Kelly broke up with her first love and spent the summer in sadness, which also affected Marco. Kelly knew Marco had gone to prison for his friend. Living through five terrible years, they had always been there for each other. This constant sense of companionship warmed their hearts. Suddenly, Marco had an audacious idea. He wanted to meet Kelly in person, but the distance almost made it impossible. Then he thought of using their sensory ability. In front of a mirror, they could see each other. God, I'm beautiful. Such a Nice face. The next day, Kelly took her car for repairs. The mechanic asked for $1,000, but Marco suspected something was off and told her to check it. It was just a loose connector. So Marco saved Kelly the money. With Kelly's company, Marco regained hope. He started tidying up his messy room, working with dedication and fixing his neglected yard.

Lucy, al darse cuenta de que John vivía al lado, lo invitó inmediatamente a su apartamento. Sin embargo, las cosas no fueron como John esperaba. Lucy solo le pidió que ayudara con algunos trabajos pesados, pero pronto comenzó a pedirle favores personales. Al día siguiente, cuando John sacaba la basura, Lucy le pasó la suya, diciendo, puedes bajarla. También. Sin esperar respuesta, cerró la puerta en el trabajo. Cuando sus medias se rompían, le pedía que le comprara un par nuevo. John se convirtió en su sirviente personal durante una semana. Lucy le pidió favores de todo tipo. Finalmente, cuando le pidió que reparara su televisor, John explotó. No soy tu sirviente. Espero que dejes de pedirme favores. Lucy trató de explicarle, pero John la interrumpió. No más favores personales. Esa noche. Después de llegar a casa, John se sintió más irritado mientras jugaba videojuegos. Al día siguiente, compró cerveza y por casualidad se encontró con Lucy en el ascensor. Ella lo invitó a su apartamento para comer pollo frito. John aceptó enseguida. Después de beber un poco, Lucy se disculpó. Sé que te pedí demasiado. John respondió educadamente, pero al despertar al día siguiente, vio a Lucy desnuda junto a él. Inmediatamente comprendió que estaba perdido.

voice_to_text: My girlfriend ditched me and drove off, leaving me behind with the butcher, who slowly turned his bloodthirsty gaze toward me. Just as he was about to strike, a gunshot rang out. He collapsed. The police had finally tracked him down. Even though the butcher died that night, my mind never recovered. 10 years passed, yet his shadow still haunted every corner of my brain. To finally conquer my inner demons, I didn't confront my fear. I became it. I dug up the butcher's old miners outfit in pickaxe and I began my own killing spree. First, I wanted revenge on my ex, the woman who abandoned me and her current husband, David. So I recreated a series of murders, making everyone believe the butcher from 10 years ago had returned. That way no suspicion would ever fall on me while I carried out my plan. One night, my ex and her best friend broke into a supermarket. I followed them inside to survive. They had no choice but to split up right then. My ex tripped and fell, a perfect chance. But her friend grabbed her and saved her. The two of them ran into a warehouse. I shoved a cabinet against the door to trap them, but breaking in was only a matter of time for me. They tried escaping through the window, but I was already waiting outside. I killed her friend first. My ex was so terrified, she bolted straight for the door and crashed into Her husband, David. I didn't get to kill her this time, but I moved on to the next phase of my plan. I called her and told her the butcher from 10 years ago was dead and the person killing now might be her husband in disguise. I said the proof was hidden in the old mine. Then I tricked her into getting in my car, planning to take her to the mine and finish her off with my pickaxe. But after investigating, her husband immediately called her and told her I was probably the real butcher and that I had serious mental issues. But even if she knew, it didn't matter. She was going to die by my pickaxe anyway. Just when I was getting excited, she grabbed the steering wheel and yanked it hard. The car crashed. I was knocked out cold. She crawled out and called her husband right away. David told her to go to the cabin in the woods. But as soon as she stepped inside, I was already there dressed as the butcher. She didn't suspect a thing. Only her husband knew about the cabin, so she assumed the butcher she was looking at was her husband.

voice_to_text: I rushed over in a panic. The front door was wide open and several masked intruders were about to burst in. Luckily, I slammed the door shut at the last moment. Then I quickly activated the home security system. Still worried, I grabbed my phone to call the police. But my house is out in the countryside and it was pouring rain outside. Police said it would take at least 30 minutes to get here. I couldn't wait that long and immediately called my security company. I never expected the person answering to be a rookie on her first day. When she heard what was happening, she panicked. Fortunately, she quickly reached out to her supervisor, Jim. He stayed calm and patiently guided me. I woke my sleeping son and prepared to flee. Jim hacked into my home security feed and spotted two men and one woman among the intruders. He told my son and me to hide, but warned us to stay away from the front door. The intruders were setting explosives. Soon, the door blew open and the intruders entered. Guided by Jim, my son and I crept away step by step, trying not to be seen. The intruders then sprayed black paint on the security cameras. After covering all the cameras, they removed their masks and stopped hiding. Then they pulled out various detection devices. Just then, Jim remembered an emergency backup camera and activated it. The intruder split up. The woman hunted for my son. And me, while the two men searched for valuables. Meanwhile, I had my son hide in the storage room's ventilation opening, while I hid in the closet. But the intruder soon found us. Detecting something with his scanner, he grabbed an axe and swung it at the wall. Soon, he smashed a large hole, but only steel support rods were inside, so he walked away in frustration. My son and I were now safe, but the wall structure seemed to give the intruder an idea. Eventually, he found a hidden door, behind which was a safe. Meanwhile, I reconnected with Jim. He told us to go to the garage and drive away. Guided by Jim, we quickly reached the garage. But unfortunately, female intruder also appeared. At that moment, I signaled my son to stay silent. Unexpectedly, the female intruder suddenly threw a flash bang grenade. The piercing explosion instantly blinded us all. Still, we dared not make a sound. Yet even then, the female intruder continued walking toward us.

voice_to_text: Hanzo and I were both sons of the general. We trained with swords together, played together and built a deep bond as brothers. But early that morning, our father summoned us. When we saw the armor that symbolized ultimate power, it was clear he planned to choose one of us as his successor. Then father handed each of us a katana. Only the one who survived could inherit his position. Out of brotherly love, I sheath my blade and gave up the claim myself. But father, disappointingly, put the armor away. Hanzo stood there, torn within her conflict. I. I never imagined my brother would actually turn on me for power. Heartbroken and disillusioned, I left home without looking back. 20 years later, father died and the funeral bells echoed through Tokyo. Living and hiding under a false identity, I finally retrieved the weapons I had prepared for years. Late that night, a fierce monster stood on the palace rooftop. It was a predator that traveled across planets and aris, hunting only the strongest warriors. Soon, its target appeared. I floated downstream on a piece of driftwood until I reached the shore, then climbed the wall using my canoe. But I never knew the invisible predator was watching my every move. Soon, I located Hanzo's position, but a samurai in the watch tower spotted me just as he was about to ring the alarm. I threw my chain and wrapped it around the bell. Suddenly, the harsh ringing echoed anyway. My presence had been exposed. Hanzo instantly became alert. The next second, several red smoke bombs exploded around me. I moved swiftly through the mist, cutting down samurai one after another. Soon only the two of us brothers remained on the battlefield. I dropped all pretenses I would make him pay in blood for what happened years ago. We clashed immediately, but Hanzo, who had lived comfortably for so long, couldn't handle a real life or death fight. Predator hid in the ceiling silently waiting for the strongest to emerge. Our battle was evenly matched. We fought from the ground to the rooftops. Hanzos katana got stuck in the wooden beam. I seized the opening and kicked him back. Hanzo desperately dodged while trying to put on our father's armor. But even then, he was still no match for me. After a fierce barrage, I cornered him. A wave of regret washed over me. I only wanted to settle the old grudge, not kill him. But a deep roar suddenly echoed behind me. I threw a smoke bomb as samurai rushed into the room and the next second they were slaughtered by the predator. Realizing I stood no chance, I tried to slip away quietly, but the predator activated its cloaking device and locked onto me using heat signatures. A grappling hook shot toward my chest and I rolled aside just in time. He launched into a brutal parkour chase across the rooftops. But as the universe's Ultimate Warrior, the Predator caught up easily. In the critical moment, I tumbled back to the shore, only to discover Hanzo wasn't dead after all. But now wasn't the time to settle our grudge. The predator suddenly appeared behind me. Hanzo blocked the attack without hesitation, but was impaled straight through. I pushed my brother aside and used my agility to get behind the predator, but my blade couldn't even pierce its armor. Enraged, the predator pinned me down. At the last second, Hanzo attacked from behind. But the small wound didn't kill the predator, it only made it furious. I gathered my last strength as we brothers struggle to stand. But the predator had already vanished, leaving only a bloodstain on the tree. It was clear it had gone back into stealth mode. We braced ourselves, watching as leaves drifted to the ground. After surviving this life and death battle, we finally buried our hatred. But Hanzo, too badly wounded, collapsed anyway. And just then, a collar suddenly snapped around my neck.

voice_to_text: The man had originally planned to drown his paralyzed wife, but as he prepared to carry out the act, he suddenly slipped, hitting his head hard on the sink and passing out cold. Seeing this, the wife panicked instantly. The bathtub faucet was still running, and with her body fully paralyzed, she couldn't move at all. It was only a matter of time before the rising water would drown her. Desperate to survive, she focused all her strength on her right foot, the only part of her body with a trace of sensation, hoping to kick open the bathtub drain. But after several desperate attempts, not only did she fail to open the drain, she accidentally broke the metal chain attached to it. At this point, she was completely hopeless. Watching the water continue to rise, nearing her mouth and nose, she quickly shifted her focus and pinned her last hope on her left hand. She tried to use the shower hose to reach and turn off the faucet, but even that was agonizingly slow. Before she could get close enough, the water had already covered half her head, leaving only her eyes above the surface. Just as she was about to drown, she suddenly mustered a final burst of strength. Though she managed to slightly turn off the faucet, the rising water still left her in a life or death situation. With her last gasp of breath slipping away, she relaxed her body and let her right foot float. Upward! Then, with a sudden kick, she finally dislodged the bathtub drain. As the water level slowly dropped, her head broke through the surface, barely escaping death. But then she made an astonishing discovery. The near death experience had somehow triggered sensation in her body. She could move like a normal person again. Quickly, she placed both hands on the edge of the tub, trying to check on her unconscious husband. But eerily, the man who had just been lying there was now nowhere to be seen.

voice_to_text: On this small island, every time a baby was born, an elderly person had to be sacrificed to maintain the population balance. As he watched his grandson being born, the grandfather resolutely chose to leap off a cliff, offering himself for the cause. But what no one expected was that right after he jumped, the doctor discovered the woman had actually given birth to twins. This meant that one grandfather's death wasn't enough. Another person would have to die. The island council immediately convened to discuss what to do. Some suggested making an exception. After all, one extra baby wouldn't drastically upset the island's balance. But the island chief firmly opposed this idea. With deadly viruses ravaging the outside world, the island was one of the last safe havens. The population of exactly 513 must not be disturbed under any circumstances. In the end, they decided to activate a point based elimination system. Each islander had a personal score. Good deeds earn points. All bad behavior LED to deductions. The council gave the residents eight days. At the end of that period, the person with the lowest score would be executed. Curly, seeing his name third from the bottom, jumped up in fear. If he ended up being chosen, his fate would be sealed. The thought alone made his legs go weak with panic. But Nick, sitting beside him, whispered not to worry. His mother was the island chief and when the time came, he promised he'd find a way. To help curly avoid elimination, second to last was an old woman. Her eccentric personality had made her unpopular with the others. Now elderly and frail, she could no longer work the fields and likely had no chance of earning more points to climb the ranking. But even so, the man at the very bottom of the list, the chubby guy, was the most innocent of them all.

voice_to_text: Estaba protegiendo al presidente. Cuando noté que el guardaespaldas detrás de mí llevaba la funda del arma abierta. Esa mínima señal me hizo sentir un peligro inmediato al ver que no parecía una mala persona. Bajé la guardia por un momento, pero al seguir observando los alrededores del presidente me di cuenta de que algo no cuadraba en el lugar. Muchos espectadores agitaban banderas de colores. Como francotirador profesional, sabía que aquello no eran solo simples banderas, también podían ser instrumentos para medir la dirección del viento. Avisé de inmediato al coronel a mi lado para que asegurara todos los puntos elevados en un radio de 2km. Los equipos de seguridad se movilizaron enseguida, pero de pronto noté que el viento se había detenido casi por completo. Otra vez el peligro me golpeó el instinto. De repente, un disparo estalló a mis espaldas. En ese instante comprendí por fin que esta misión de protección presidencial, era en realidad una trampa cuidadosamente montada contra mí. Por suerte, reaccioné a tiempo y salté por la ventana. Ahora sabía con claridad que debía salir de ese lugar cuanto antes, que ya me habían convertido en un fugitivo buscado en toda la ciudad. Las fuerzas de tierra, mar y aire tenían sus ojos puestos en mí. No había corrido mucho cuando choqué de frente con un policía. Para evitar que descubriera mi identidad, lo neutralicé rápidamente. Le supliqué que me creyera que me había entendido una trampa. En un impulso, tomé su arma Robé su coche patrulla y escapé del lugar a toda velocidad, las calles estaban llenas de patrullas buscándome y además seguía herido por un disparo anterior. Para despistar a la policía, entré en un túnel de lavado. Mientras el coche era limpiado, me pasé al asiento trasero y me vendé la herida lo más rápido que pude. Después salí del lugar sin perder un segundo. Pronto la policía localizó mi vehículo y me acercó bajo un gran puente. Al ver cómo llegaban más patrullas, metí marcha atrás y me lancé directamente al río. Cuando los agentes alcanzaron la orilla, ya había desaparecido bajo la cobertura de un barco grande. Conseguí eludir temporalmente la persecución. Aún así, no podía relajarme. Robé otro coche cerca del puente, sabiendo que toda la atención policial seguía concentrada en el río. Al poco tiempo logré salir de la ciudad. Lo primero que hice fue ir a casa de mi exnovia porque ella era doctora. Cuando me vio, se asustó. Ya había visto las noticias sobre mi orden de arresto. Por suerte, los lazos del pasado aún pesaban. Finalmente me abrió la puerta y comenzó a atender mi herida de bala. Durante la conversación, supe que quien había caído no era el presidente, sino el arzobispo que estaba a su lado. Al comprender que todo había sido una trampa para inculparme, decidí descubrir quién estaba detrás de toda aquella conspiración

Cada día, el director de la prisión prepara una gran comida en la cocina y luego baja toda la plataforma, desde el nivel más alto hasta el más bajo. En cada nivel solo hay dos prisioneros. Ellos esperan todos los días esa mesa que cae del cielo. Pero la realidad no es tan bonita. Cuando la comida llega a su nivel, ya ha sido destrozada por los de arriba. voice_to_text: As a row of sharp spears struck the ground, an invisible barrier instantly formed. The charging herd of yak sense danger, panicked and turned to flee, unaware that a sheer precipice lay ahead. But by the time they realized the peril, it was too late. Witnessing comrades tumbling into the abyss one after another, the Yak King understood he'd fallen into a human trap. To avenge his clan's tragic deaths, the Yak King turned and charged furiously toward the hunters. Along the way, he collided with a frail youth named Jack, very son of the tribes chieftain. Seeing his son in peril, the chieftain hurled his spear with all his might, driving it deep into the bull's belly, but blinded by vengeance, did not halt. For the pain owing to drag Jack into the abyss, the bull ultimately hurled him over the cliff. Everyone rushed nervously to the cliff's edge. Fortunately, Jack did not fall to his death on the spot, but clung desperately to a protruding rock on the cliff edge. Yet he remained over 30 feet from the rim. Rescuing his son from the smooth cliff face proved no easy task. The father screamed frantically from the cliff's edge. Suddenly, the rock shattered. Under the strain, under the horrified stares of the crowd, Jack plummeted once more into the abyss. Watching his son fall, the chieftain sank into profound despair, intending to end his own life. For solace, his tribe pulled him back, for as their leader, he Bore the responsibility for all. The father cried out from the cliff's edge all night long, yet never heard his son's reply. When the truth was revealed, the father was overcome with grief, forced to accept his son's death. But fate showed mercy to Jack once more. He did not plunge into the abyss, but crashed onto a protruding ledge. After an unknown period of unconsciousness, a vulture landed on the boy, savagely pecking at his lips. The excruciating pain jolted Jack awake. But when he looked down, Jack was terrified by what he saw. Staring at the bottomless chasm below, Jack could only try to climb upward, but unexpectedly his foot slipped. He found himself dangling in midair once again. This time, there was no foothold and only exhaustion and death awaited him. Just when all hope seemed lost, a violent storm suddenly struck. Torrential rain cascaded down the cliff face. Jack instantly saw a glimmer of hope for survival. As more and more water accumulated, he gritted his teeth and held on until the very last moment. Finally, when his strength was completely drained, Jack suddenly let go.

The maid quietly urged her family to sneak out while they still had the chance. Suddenly, the homeowner's daughter appeared at the foot of the stairs. Turned out, the little girl wanted to camp on the lawn that night. In that moment, the hiding family quickly crawled under the sofa, narrowly avoiding being seen by the wealthy household. But a new challenge awaited them. How would they escape? Now? The daughter had settled comfortably in her tent outside, while the rich couple relaxed on the living room sofa above them. The hidden family held their breath, not daring to make a sound. When the couple finally drifted off to sleep, the family carefully slid out from under the sofa, towed toward the garage, and slipped out through the back door of the villa. As the saying goes, a heavy rain reveals the true gap between in rich and poor. The wealthier you are, the higher you live. While the poor family descended downhill, swept along like debris toward the depth of the city's drainage system. When they finally returned home, the shock was overwhelming. Their modest basement home had been destroyed, the water level rising to their waists, and dirty water gushed endlessly from the toilet. Yet the little the tent of the rich family outside remained untouched. Not a single drop touched it. It was as if some lucky charm had shielded them from the storm. Staring at the ruins, the eldest son silently vowed, no matter what it take, he would climb into the upper class one day and give his family the life they truly deserve.
